    "body": "# Problem\n\nTo get a plugin-specific data/cache/log dir, currently these steps are required. Although it's not a huge amount of code, it's not very obvious what patterns plugins are supposed to follow for storing their data.\n\n```lua\n--- @param kind string\nlocal function ensuredir(kind)\n  local dir = vim.fn.stdpath(kind)\n  local plugdir = vim.fs.joinpath(dir, 'my-plugin')\n  vim.fn.mkdir(plugdir, 'p')\n  return plugdir\nend\n\nlocal function plugin_datadir()\n  return ensuredir('data')\nend\n\nlocal function plugin_cachedir()\n  return ensuredir('cache')\nend\n```\n\n# Expected behavior\n\n### Option 1\n\nAdd an optional arg to `stdpath()`, which only works for the \"data\"/\"cache\"/\"log\" cases? Then the above code would become:\n\n```lua\nlocal function plugin_datadir()\n  return vim.fn.stdpath('data', 'my-plugin')\nend\n\nlocal function plugin_cachedir()\n  return vim.fn.stdpath('cache', 'my-plugin')\nend\n```\n\n### Option 2\n\nFit this into [plugin namespaces](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/992#issuecomment-2577779050) somehow. Maybe:\n\n```\nlocal myplugin = vim.ns.new('my-plugin')\nlocal datadir = myplugin:sdtpath('data')\nlocal cachedir = myplugin:sdtpath('cache')\n```",
